-Mama?
-[KNOCKING]

963
00:38:21,419 --> 00:38:24,045
-I'm coming in. Okay?
-[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

964
00:38:32,470 --> 00:38:34,597
[BOTH YELLING]

965
00:38:34,681 --> 00:38:37,517
-You gave me a heart attack!
-[LAUGHING]

966
00:38:37,601 --> 00:38:40,353
Ah, your face! Hysterical!

967
00:38:40,437 --> 00:38:42,229
I'm a city dweller.

968
00:38:42,313 --> 00:38:45,190
So images in the ocean all
come from monster movies.

969
00:38:45,274 --> 00:38:47,317
-Oh…
-Squid from outer space

970
00:38:47,401 --> 00:38:49,069
with lasers for eyes.

971
00:38:49,153 --> 00:38:51,071
Godzilla and Nazi U-boats.

972
00:38:51,155 --> 00:38:53,073
It was always so easy to get you.

973
00:38:53,157 --> 00:38:55,742
Oh, yes, I am particularly gullible.

974
00:38:55,826 --> 00:38:57,119
Yeah. Hello, Abe?

975
00:38:57,203 --> 00:38:58,787
Upton Sinclair here.

976
00:38:58,871 --> 00:39:00,788
-[LAUGHING]
-Well, you sounded just like him.

977
00:39:00,872 --> 00:39:02,790
Not that I know what he sounds like.

978
00:39:02,874 --> 00:39:05,251
Oh, it's nice to joke
around with you again

979
00:39:05,335 --> 00:39:07,586
-after all these years.
-[LAUGHS] I have to admit,

980
00:39:07,670 --> 00:39:10,381
seeing you in a swimsuit
takes some getting used to.

981
00:39:10,465 --> 00:39:12,800
[LAUGHS] Well, it's Florida, Abe.

982
00:39:12,884 --> 00:39:15,427
It's a swimsuit or nothing.

983
00:39:15,511 --> 00:39:17,304
Upton Sinclair.

984
00:39:17,388 --> 00:39:19,640
-Just like him.
-[CHUCKLES]

985
00:39:21,183 --> 00:39:23,101
[GROANS]

986
00:39:23,185 --> 00:39:25,187
♪♪

987
00:39:27,689 --> 00:39:29,524
Whoo!

988
00:39:29,608 --> 00:39:31,151
ABE: Vito Vincenzo.

989
00:39:31,235 --> 00:39:32,777
-That was it!
-ABE: We were gonna unionize

990
00:39:32,861 --> 00:39:35,572
the Lower East Side
fruit vendors if it killed us,

991
00:39:35,656 --> 00:39:37,406
and Vito was the lone holdout.

992
00:39:37,490 --> 00:39:39,992
-How we harangued that poor man.
-"How could you do this

993
00:39:40,076 --> 00:39:41,118
"to your fellow fruit men?

994
00:39:41,202 --> 00:39:42,661
Have you no shame, sir?"

995
00:39:42,745 --> 00:39:44,413
[CHUCKLES]: We called
him "the one bad apple."

996
00:39:44,497 --> 00:39:46,999
We put…
we put "union" signs on his lemons!

997
00:39:47,083 --> 00:39:48,709
On each individual lemon.

998
00:39:48,793 --> 00:39:51,420
We had a good deal of time on our hands.

999
00:39:53,047 --> 00:39:56,340
It's so quiet here. Just the ocean.

1000
00:39:56,424 --> 00:39:59,051
ASHER: I love it. I just love it.

1001
00:39:59,135 --> 00:40:02,346
You know, I always had a
hard time picturing you here.

1002
00:40:02,430 --> 00:40:04,473
-Why?
-You're so New York.

1003
00:40:04,557 --> 00:40:06,767
A man of the city.

1004
00:40:06,851 --> 00:40:10,521
I wouldn't survive in that
city for five minutes now.

1005
00:40:10,605 --> 00:40:13,191
Look at what I have here: sun, surf,

1006
00:40:13,275 --> 00:40:14,399
freedom!

1007
00:40:14,483 --> 00:40:15,817
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

1008
00:40:15,901 --> 00:40:18,361
I open when I want; I close when I want.

1009
00:40:18,445 --> 00:40:20,447
I haven't put on socks in weeks,

1010
00:40:20,531 --> 00:40:22,532
and every night there's
a beautiful sunset,

1011
00:40:22,616 --> 00:40:24,284
and I never miss it.

1012
00:40:24,368 --> 00:40:26,495
It's paradise.

1013
00:40:28,455 --> 00:40:33,083
You know… I'm not teaching anymore.

1014
00:40:33,167 --> 00:40:34,501
You're kidding. What happened?

1015
00:40:34,585 --> 00:40:36,503
I lost my taste for it.

1016
00:40:36,587 --> 00:40:39,798
It didn't seem important,
what I was doing there.

1017
00:40:39,882 --> 00:40:41,800
So what are you doing now?

1018
00:40:41,884 --> 00:40:43,969
I've been trying to figure that out.

1019
00:40:44,053 --> 00:40:47,431
I've been missing the
old me, the man you knew.

1020
00:40:47,515 --> 00:40:49,892
I… I thought I could get that fire back,

1021
00:40:49,976 --> 00:40:51,726
I could care about something,

1022
00:40:51,810 --> 00:40:53,728
be involved in something meaningful.

1023
00:40:53,812 --> 00:40:57,357
-You know what I mean?
-I sell bait now, so no.

1024
00:40:57,441 --> 00:40:59,067
[ABE CHUCKLES]

1025
00:40:59,151 --> 00:41:01,861
I met some young people in a bar.

1026
00:41:01,945 --> 00:41:04,113
They talked a lot like we used to talk.

1027
00:41:04,197 --> 00:41:06,741
Lots of jargon and mentions of Trotsky.

1028
00:41:06,825 --> 00:41:07,825
Trotsky's still a thing?

1029
00:41:07,909 --> 00:41:09,202
They wanted to start a paper.

1030
00:41:09,286 --> 00:41:10,661
Everyone wants to start a paper.

1031
00:41:10,745 --> 00:41:12,579
-We wanted to start a paper.
-I thought

1032
00:41:12,663 --> 00:41:15,123
maybe I could help
them achieve their goals,

1033
00:41:15,207 --> 00:41:17,751
make a difference, but…
after a few weeks,

1034
00:41:17,835 --> 00:41:20,254
I realized they were
just a bunch of idiots.

1035
00:41:20,338 --> 00:41:22,047
All young people are
just a bunch of idiots.

1036
00:41:22,131 --> 00:41:23,924
They couldn't focus or spell

1037
00:41:24,008 --> 00:41:25,842
or form a coherent thought.

1038
00:41:25,926 --> 00:41:27,636
They think "It's the '60s, man"

1039
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:29,512
is a manifesto of some sort.

1040
00:41:29,596 --> 00:41:32,807
To them, all you have to do is
not bathe, and you're a rebel.

1041
00:41:32,891 --> 00:41:34,892
Well, there we differed.
We always bathed.

1042
00:41:34,976 --> 00:41:37,604
We did. We smelled wonderful.

1043
00:41:39,022 --> 00:41:41,065
You really don't miss New York?

1044
00:41:41,149 --> 00:41:42,316
Not at all.

1045
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:43,693
Have you been back?

1046
00:41:45,612 --> 00:41:47,362
You mean since I was blacklisted

1047
00:41:47,446 --> 00:41:49,364
and my last play closed without opening?

1048
00:41:49,448 --> 00:41:50,865
No, no, I have not.

1049
00:41:50,949 --> 00:41:53,118
Things are different now.

1050
00:41:53,202 --> 00:41:54,953
I have a life here.

1051
00:41:55,037 --> 00:41:56,955
You were such a wonderful writer.

1052
00:41:57,039 --> 00:41:58,456
Do you write at all?

1053
00:41:58,540 --> 00:42:00,125
[CHUCKLES]: Now? No.

1054
00:42:00,209 --> 00:42:02,127
Why not? After all you've been through,

1055
00:42:02,211 --> 00:42:04,629
-you must have a great story in you…
-Abe.

1056
00:42:04,713 --> 00:42:07,464
I gave the theater all I
have, and it sent me away.

1057
00:42:07,548 --> 00:42:09,049
I know, I know, it…

1058
00:42:09,133 --> 00:42:12,219
I was one of the most successful
playwrights on Broadway.

1059
00:42:12,303 --> 00:42:14,805
Every one of my shows made money.

1060
00:42:14,889 --> 00:42:16,515
I won the Pulitzer Prize.

1061
00:42:16,599 --> 00:42:19,059
The critics hailed me as
the American Chekhov.

1062
00:42:19,143 --> 00:42:21,520
And then one schmuck
calls me a communist,

1063
00:42:21,604 --> 00:42:23,479
and poof, over!

1064
00:42:23,563 --> 00:42:26,232
My friends… gone.
My agent, my producer… gone.

1065
00:42:26,316 --> 00:42:29,403
Twenty years to build a life;
two months to watch it go.

1066
00:42:31,738 --> 00:42:33,740
The theater broke my heart.

1067
00:42:34,741 --> 00:42:37,994
I wish… there was s… something…

1068
00:42:38,078 --> 00:42:39,746
I could have done.

1069
00:42:39,830 --> 00:42:41,789
What? Get up in front of McCarthy

1070
00:42:41,873 --> 00:42:43,832
and tell him the fruit stand story?

1071
00:42:43,916 --> 00:42:45,917
Tell him you were a good man. Tell him…

1072
00:42:46,001 --> 00:42:47,252
I wasn't a communist?

1073
00:42:47,336 --> 00:42:48,545
I was.

1074
00:42:48,629 --> 00:42:50,255
[QUIETLY]: No.

1075
00:42:50,339 --> 00:42:51,965
You were a teacher.

1076
00:42:52,049 --> 00:42:53,550
You had a young family.

1077
00:42:53,634 --> 00:42:56,219
What good would it do
to take you down with me?

1078
00:42:56,303 --> 00:42:58,639
I would have happily taken the chance.

1079
00:42:59,682 --> 00:43:00,849
I know.

1080
00:43:01,891 --> 00:43:03,309
You know, every night

1081
00:43:03,393 --> 00:43:05,394
I lock up this kiosk, I go home,

1082
00:43:05,478 --> 00:43:08,356
I lay in my bed, and I think

1083
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:12,109
"Maybe tomorrow when I go back,

1084
00:43:12,193 --> 00:43:14,362
"it won't be there."

1085
00:43:14,446 --> 00:43:16,530
"Someone will have stolen it,"

1086
00:43:16,614 --> 00:43:17,823
burned it down."

1087
00:43:17,907 --> 00:43:19,741
Sometimes I don't even lock it.

1088
00:43:19,825 --> 00:43:21,910
Give the thieves a fighting chance.

1089
00:43:23,454 --> 00:43:26,915
But… every morning I get up,

1090
00:43:26,999 --> 00:43:29,042
and when I walk back up the beach,

1091
00:43:29,126 --> 00:43:30,752
there it is.

1092
00:43:32,171 --> 00:43:34,964
Shining testament to my failure.

1093
00:43:35,048 --> 00:43:36,633
You didn't fail.

1094
00:43:36,717 --> 00:43:38,467
Others failed you.

1095
00:43:38,551 --> 00:43:40,135
A lot of those people are still there.

1096
00:43:40,219 --> 00:43:42,805
In New York, in the theater.

1097
00:43:42,889 --> 00:43:46,600
And I wear flowered shorts to work.

1098
00:43:46,684 --> 00:43:48,519
So, New York…

1099
00:43:50,062 --> 00:43:52,315
New York and I are done.

1100
00:43:55,109 --> 00:43:57,735
You know they're doing
one of my plays here?

1101
00:43:57,819 --> 00:43:59,070
In Miami?

1102
00:43:59,154 --> 00:44:00,571
Local community group.

1103
00:44:00,655 --> 00:44:02,323
[LAUGHS] Which play?

1104
00:44:02,407 --> 00:44:04,033
<i>Pillar of Salt.</i>

1105
00:44:04,117 --> 00:44:06,577
This is a very ambitious
community theater.

1106
00:44:06,661 --> 00:44:08,579
Yeah. They did a rousing
production of Bloomer Girl

1107
00:44:08,663 --> 00:44:10,581
last year, so I'm sure
they're very qualified.

1108
00:44:10,665 --> 00:44:11,999
[ABE CHUCKLES]

1109
00:44:12,083 --> 00:44:14,335
You should go see it. I'll go with you.

1110
00:44:14,419 --> 00:44:16,003
-We'll go together.
-Abe.

1111
00:44:17,254 --> 00:44:18,923
No.

1112
00:44:21,759 --> 00:44:23,009
Huh.

1113
00:44:23,093 --> 00:44:25,554
I believe we need to restock.

1114
00:44:31,644 --> 00:44:34,270
It's nice to see an
old friend again, Abe.

1115
00:44:34,354 --> 00:44:36,730
[ABE CHUCKLES]

1116
00:44:36,814 --> 00:44:38,900
You're still a mensch.

1117
00:44:41,236 --> 00:44:43,071
Gives me hope.

1118
00:44:49,577 --> 00:44:51,328
Looks good.

1119
00:44:51,412 --> 00:44:53,329
Looks really good.

1120
00:44:53,413 --> 00:44:55,415
Some tables, a few chairs,

1121
00:44:55,499 --> 00:44:57,500
and this place is a club.

1122
00:44:57,584 --> 00:44:59,210
Yeah.

1123
00:44:59,294 --> 00:45:01,963
You want to show a
little enthusiasm there?

1124
00:45:02,047 --> 00:45:03,756
Home stretch, pal.

1125
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:05,592
You know, Mei got me that liquor license.

1126
00:45:05,676 --> 00:45:07,177
How the hell did she do that?

1127
00:45:07,261 --> 00:45:08,595
How the hell does she do anything?

1128
00:45:08,679 --> 00:45:10,596
-She just did it.
-So?

1129
00:45:10,680 --> 00:45:12,431
Sometimes you need a little help.

1130
00:45:12,515 --> 00:45:13,765
No.

1131
00:45:13,849 --> 00:45:16,351
I have to sink or swim on my own here.

1132
00:45:16,435 --> 00:45:18,353
I played second fiddle to
Midge our whole marriage,

1133
00:45:18,437 --> 00:45:19,855
and I just can't do that again.

1134
00:45:19,939 --> 00:45:21,857
Then you need to start
picking different women.

1135
00:45:21,941 --> 00:45:23,859
-[SCOFFS]
-You pick conductors.

1136
00:45:23,943 --> 00:45:26,487
You need someone who plays the triangle.

1137
00:45:26,571 --> 00:45:28,905
Triangle girls are boring.

1138
00:45:29,906 --> 00:45:31,741
Imogene?

1139
00:45:33,743 --> 00:45:35,829
Hi, honey!

1140
00:45:38,748 --> 00:45:40,750
-What are you…
-We just painted that. Shit.

1141
00:45:40,834 --> 00:45:43,628
ARCHIE: Yeah. She does that.

1142
00:45:43,712 --> 00:45:45,213
Good color.

1143
00:45:45,297 --> 00:45:46,756
Right, honey?

1144
00:45:46,840 --> 00:45:48,840
We could paint the
living room that color.

1145
00:45:48,924 --> 00:45:50,217
Because I am…

1146
00:45:50,301 --> 00:45:52,135
Just as terrifying the second time.

1147
00:45:52,219 --> 00:45:55,138
These are your children, Archie.

1148
00:45:55,222 --> 00:45:56,890
I just thought, since
you're not home anymore,

1149
00:45:56,974 --> 00:45:58,892
you might forget who they
are and what they look like.

1150
00:45:58,976 --> 00:46:02,145
And this is the reason you
have those three children.

1151
00:46:02,229 --> 00:46:04,397
Again, just to jog your memory.

1152
00:46:04,481 --> 00:46:06,148
You don't think you're
being a little dramatic?

1153
00:46:06,232 --> 00:46:08,192
Am I? Maybe. People do weird things

1154
00:46:08,276 --> 00:46:09,860
when they've been in
isolation for too long.

1155
00:46:09,944 --> 00:46:12,279
You're hardly in isolation.
Your mother's there.

1156
00:46:12,363 --> 00:46:14,114
The kids are there. And, by the way,

1157
00:46:14,198 --> 00:46:15,533
you wrote the wrong name
on one of those pictures.

1158
00:46:15,617 --> 00:46:18,452
Unless you changed Eric
to Pete while I was out.

1159
00:46:18,536 --> 00:46:20,371
Ha! That was a test.
Thank God you passed.

1160
00:46:20,455 --> 00:46:21,015
Look, Imogene…

1161
00:46:21,099 --> 00:46:23,374
What do you think you
have to contribute here, Joel?

1162
00:46:23,458 --> 00:46:25,208
-Nothing.
-[EXHALES]

1163
00:46:25,292 --> 00:46:27,418
I'll be over there.

1164
00:46:27,502 --> 00:46:30,088
Can we please discuss
this when I get home?

1165
00:46:30,172 --> 00:46:32,090
Oh, you're coming home?
How nice. When will that be?

1166
00:46:32,174 --> 00:46:33,424
-Tonight.
-What time tonight?

1167
00:46:33,508 --> 00:46:34,634
I'm not sure.

1168
00:46:34,718 --> 00:46:35,969
-I want to be up.
-11:00.

1169
00:46:36,053 --> 00:46:37,971
-Eleven o'clock. Tonight.
-Yes.

1170
00:46:38,055 --> 00:46:41,724
I'll powder my nose in anticipation.

1171
00:46:41,808 --> 00:46:44,351
You had to bring everything
down with you, didn't you?

1172
00:46:44,435 --> 00:46:46,854
Imogene.

1173
00:46:47,855 --> 00:46:49,189
Go after her, Archie.

1174
00:46:49,273 --> 00:46:50,816
No.

1175
00:46:50,900 --> 00:46:52,067
Better to let her cool down.

1176
00:46:52,151 --> 00:46:53,277
I'll deal with it tonight.

1177
00:46:53,361 --> 00:46:54,278
You sure?

1178
00:46:54,362 --> 00:46:56,029
I can hit these clubs alone.

1179
00:46:56,113 --> 00:46:57,614
What fun would that be?

1180
00:46:57,698 --> 00:46:59,950
It's not for fun. It's research.

1181
00:47:00,034 --> 00:47:01,867
Checking out the competition.

1182
00:47:01,951 --> 00:47:03,703
Oh. So no drinking.

1183
00:47:03,787 --> 00:47:05,371
Oh, no, there will be drinking.

1184
00:47:05,455 --> 00:47:08,124
But sad, un-fun drinking.

1185
00:47:08,208 --> 00:47:11,085
Perfect night for that.

1186
00:47:11,169 --> 00:47:12,837
MAN: Nothing will be there tomorrow.

1187
00:47:12,921 --> 00:47:14,672
WOMAN: And the girls
have their piano lessons

1188
00:47:14,756 --> 00:47:16,465
-down on 12th Street.
-No pianos,

1189
00:47:16,549 --> 00:47:17,967
no lessons, no streets.

1190
00:47:18,051 --> 00:47:19,634
-WOMAN: You're trying to scare me.
-Yes, I have to.

1191
00:47:19,718 --> 00:47:22,137
WOMAN: You said the same thing
when the protestors marched in the square

1192
00:47:22,221 --> 00:47:23,555
and when the cinema showed the film

1193
00:47:23,639 --> 00:47:24,806
about the young lovers in French.

1194
00:47:24,890 --> 00:47:26,057
"It's the end of everything."

1195
00:47:26,141 --> 00:47:27,475
But it wasn't, was it?

1196
00:47:27,559 --> 00:47:29,394
MAN: This is something
entirely different.

1197
00:47:29,478 --> 00:47:31,730
Not slow degeneration, now.

1198
00:47:31,814 --> 00:47:34,983
Complete and utter
destruction coming like lightning

1199
00:47:35,067 --> 00:47:38,068
in the space of an
hour by the hand of God.

1200
00:47:38,152 --> 00:47:40,821
-[JAZZ PLAYING]
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1201
00:47:40,905 --> 00:47:42,573
Hello.

1202
00:47:44,325 --> 00:47:45,993
Now, this is more like it.

1203
00:47:46,077 --> 00:47:47,828
Much classier than the last place.

1204
00:47:47,912 --> 00:47:49,455
Your feet don't stick to the floor.

1205
00:47:49,539 --> 00:47:50,706
Let's put that on the list.

1206
00:47:50,790 --> 00:47:52,875
Clean the floor once in a while.

1207
00:47:54,293 --> 00:47:55,794
Whiskey, neat.

1208
00:47:55,878 --> 00:47:57,545
-Two of 'em.
-How much?

1209
00:47:57,629 --> 00:47:59,255
-Three dollars.
-For two whiskeys?

1210
00:47:59,339 --> 00:48:00,989
Do they come with the distillery?

1211
00:48:02,426 --> 00:48:03,426
So, not a comedy club.

1212
00:48:03,510 --> 00:48:06,012
I'll say.

1213
00:48:06,096 --> 00:48:07,096
What are you doing?

1214
00:48:07,180 --> 00:48:08,264
Make mine a double.

1215
00:48:08,348 --> 00:48:09,474
You took your ring off.

